Subject: New message from "Posh Sidekick"
Created At: 2024-03-09T23:00:29Z

Threads:
Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-09T23:25:45Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Chrissy, Thank you for your interest in Poshsidekick! Here are some
answers to your questions: Poshsidekick is currently only available as a mobile
app and you can use it on your phone. And it is optimized for closets with up to
5,000 listings. While it may work for larger closets, we can't guarantee full
sharing coverage for closets exceeding this size. Unfortunately, you can't
control how often your closet is shared manually. The app shares items
throughout the day automatically. Also, Poshsidekick doesn't currently have a
feature to automatically remove inventory from other platforms when an item
sells elsewhere. It primarily focuses on automating tasks on Poshmark. The merge
with the cross-listing is ongoing, and once completed, you'll have access to
both Poshmark automation and cross-listing features in one app. However, the
merged app isn't available yet but you can try our cross-listing app in the
meantime to familiarize yourself with its features. Here's the link to download
the cross-listing app, which you can try for free for 7 days:
https://app.crosslisting.com/ [https://app.crosslisting.com/] You can use it on
your computer and download it on your phone. If you have any further questions,
feel free to ask. Thank you! Best, Julia

audience. As an affiliate, you'll have access to a range of benefits, including:
* Free access to Sidekick's premium features. * Affiliate credits for each
successful referral. * Exclusive promotional materials and support from our team
We believe that your unique perspective and reach can make a significant
contribution to our mission of empowering sellers and improving their selling
experiences. If you're interested in exploring this opportunity further or have
any questions, please don't hesitate to reach out. We would love to talk about
how we can expand our partnership to meet your specific needs and preferences.
Thank you for considering this opportunity, and we look forward to the

during the trial period. 3. Commission: For every subscription, you'll get a 25%
commission on the first purchase. 4. Content Creation: Promote Posh Sidekick by
creating 2 videos or reels per month, and in return, enjoy a free service every
month. Please download the Sidekick app from the below link and create your
account: PlayStore Link:¬†Click Here

after the item gets relisted. Yes, you can skip items that you don't want to be
relisted. There is an option under the relisting setting, "Skip Items From
Relist". Please use that feature. Please note that only 400 follow/unfollow will
be done per day and this limitation applies to all of our clients. We are always
open to answer of your any queries. Have a great day! Best Regards, Simon

wanted to introduce you to an exciting collaboration opportunity with Posh
Sidekick. Posh Sidekick offers a range of features tailored to empower Poshmark
sellers: ¬∑¬†Automated Sharing:¬†Save time by automating the sharing of your
listings across various channels, including self-sharing, party sharing,
community sharing, and share-back. ¬∑¬†Relisting:¬†Automatically repost old
listings to keep your inventory fresh and visible. ¬∑¬†Automated Live
Auctions:¬†Run silent auctions for your listings, creating an interactive
experience for your followers. ¬∑¬†Background Remover: Easily create
professional-looking listing photos with clean backgrounds. ¬∑¬†Closet
Snapshot:¬†Keep your closet organized to reflect your brand identity. ¬∑¬†Offer to
Likers:¬†Send customizable offers to likers to attract more buyers and increase
conversion rates. ¬∑¬†Follow and Unfollow:¬†Manage your following list effectively
to target potential buyers. ¬∑¬†Randomization:¬†Mimic natural sharing behavior to
avoid detection by platforms. ¬∑¬†Promoted Listings:¬†Increase visibility and
exposure to potential buyers with targeted promotions. For more information
about our app, please click this guide:¬†https://poshsidekick.com/guide/
[https://poshsidekick.com/guide/] We believe that your expertise in fashion and
reselling could make a big impact on the success of these features. We'd love to
collaborate with you to showcase Posh Sidekick to your audience and demonstrate
its benefits. If you're interested in learning more about this collaboration
opportunity or exploring how Posh Sidekick can benefit your audience, please
reach out. We look forward to the possibility of working together! Best regards,
Gail

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-09T04:07:39Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Meg, Thank you for reaching out and for your positive feedback. Relisting
can automatically re-post old listings with the Relists feature. This feature
allows you to choose how old a listing must be before it is relisted. You can
choose from 15, 30, 60, or 90 days as the age limit for a listing to be
relisted. Once the listing reaches the age limit, The app will delete the
listing and repost it as a brand-new listing. This ensures that the item gets
treated as a new listing in the algorithm, increasing its visibility. Please
turn on the Relists feature to make the most of your listings. Regarding the
duplicate listings, occasionally you may see a duplicate listing, you may use
this tool to remove them by scanning for the duplicates, you can detect these
duplicates by checking the Title, Price, Size, Colors, or Description. If any
duplicates are visible after scanning, swipe left on each duplicate, and you
will be able to either VIEW or DELETE the listing. For more information and a
guide kindly click this link https://poshsidekick.com/guide/
[https://poshsidekick.com/guide/] I hope this clarifies your concern. If you
have any other questions or need further assistance, please don‚Äôt hesitate to
reach out. Best regards, Gail

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-15T18:10:25Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hi Jennifer, Thank you for your email! Kindly be aware that it's not the entire
women category, what we meant is the customize category that you have created
and named as "No discounts". It is in your My Categories section which is under
Tools tab. I suggest following the below steps: 1. Click on Tools Tab (bottom
part of the screen) 2. Tap My Categories, then click on the customize category
"No Discounts" 3. Check if the items are there, and you will also see that you
have selected "Women" under Departments Then after checking, and confirming if
there are items are included there you can proceed checking in your offers
setting. 1. Go to Settings Page 2. Scroll down to Offers section 3. Under Offer
Filters, you will see "No discounts", just above "Add Offer Rules For My
Category" 4. Click on the "No Discounts", then you'll see that you have made an
exception for it and enabled the "Do not send OTL for this category" feature. I
suggest deleting the customized category of "No discounts" that you have
created, and utilize the offer filter which is "Add offer rules for specific
items" instead for items that you don't want the app to send an offer. Thank
you! Kind regards, Ana

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-09T00:48:05Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Jennifer, Thank you for reaching out! I understand you‚Äôre having some
concerns about the offer settings. Let me clarify how it works. The 15-minute
interval setting means that the app checks every 15 minutes to see if there are
any new likes and sends out offers accordingly. So, it‚Äôs possible that a like
could have happened just a minute ago, and an offer was sent out because the
15-minute interval had just ended. If you‚Äôre noticing that most items with new
likes are not receiving offers, it might be helpful to adjust your settings. We
suggest disabling the ‚ÄòRandomized OTL‚Äô and ‚ÄòRelist‚Äô options and adding a
randomized delay of 1-15 minutes to the normal ‚ÄòOTL‚Äô and ‚ÄòRelisting‚Äô times. This
should help ensure that offers are sent out more consistently to new likers. If
you continue to experience issues or have any other questions, please don‚Äôt
hesitate to reach out. kind regards, Mary

Body:
Hi Vi, Thank you for informing us! Upon checking, your account was on Soft Ban.
Please don't share your closet or add listings while the app is sharing to avoid
a Soft ban. Kindly note that it lasts for 2‚Äì3 hours This is because Poshmark
sometimes counts this as a lot of activity in your closet. Rest assured that the
app will automatically resume in sharing once the restriction is lifted. To
prevent this from happening again, I suggest turning off the app's sharing
features or changing the share speed to slow, before sharing or adding new items
to your closet. Once you've finished sharing/adding items, you can turn the

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-08T17:06:03Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hi Lisa, Thanks for reaching out. Please be advised to unlink and relink your
closet before you do a closet snapshot. Here's how to use Closet Snapshot:
‚Ä¢¬†Turn "Self Share" OFF. ‚Ä¢¬†Organize your closet manually by sharing each item
one by one until it's in the order you prefer. ‚Ä¢¬†Once your closet is organized,
go back to Posh Sidekick and click on "Closet Snapshot". ‚Ä¢¬†Under "Share
Options", select "Share in reverse". From now on, every time there's a share
session, your closet will share in the order you selected. If your closet gets
jumbled for any reason, there's a button next to the Closet Snapshot button
labeled ‚ÄúPut Your Closet Back in Order". Clicking this button will give you the
option to: ‚Ä¢ Continue sharing throughout the day. ‚Ä¢ Be notified via push
notification when the process is completed. After the notification, sharing will
stop until you turn it back on. It's important to note that once you select what
to do after putting your closet back in order, the process will begin
immediately and cannot be stopped until it's complete. We hope this helps. Best,
Kate

are still being shared, it might be because they‚Äôre not properly tagged as
‚Äúsold‚Äù on Poshmark. image.png
[https://d33v4339jhl8k0.cloudfront.net/inline/106277/81144f038b2e3a7cada534b8c2b0d5916eae62d2/a99cddd0faa079a0ac475c0392913bd20d797471/image.png]
Here‚Äôs what you can do: 1. Log in to Poshmark and go to ‚ÄúMy Closet‚Äù. 2. Click on
the listing you want to update. 3. Click ‚ÄúEdit Listing‚Äù. 4. Scroll to the very
bottom to ‚ÄúAvailability‚Äù. 5. Click the dropdown and select ‚ÄúNot for Sale‚Äù. 6.
Click ‚ÄúUpdate‚Äù. This should prevent your sold items from being shared. If you
continue to experience issues, please let us know. We‚Äôre here to help! Kind
regards, Mary

Subject: Re:
Created At: 2024-03-07T11:07:01Z

Threads:
Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-07T16:12:42Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hi Karen, Thanks for responding. Please be advised to turn off the sharing
features of the app if you wish to manually follow and share so that you won't
be soft banned. Once you've finished, you can then turn the sharing features
back on. A soft ban means that your closet is temporarily blocked from sharing
or following by Poshmark due to excessive activity. This can occur if you
manually share or add new items while the app is already sharing your listings
or if you exceed the daily limits set by Poshmark. It's important to note that
this is not a serious issue, and it does not put your account in any danger. The
soft ban is simply an automated action taken by Poshmark, and it can sometimes
trigger without warning for minor reasons. Rest assured that our app "Posh
Sidekick" has built-in safety measures to handle situations like this, and
typically, the issue is resolved within 2 to 3 hours. Thank you. Best, Kate

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-07T02:00:37Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Hazel, My apologies for the confusion. Let me clarify how the party share
feature works. Upon checking, it appears that the app is alternating between
party-sharing and self-sharing. During the first three party shares, the app
performs both self-shares and party shares. However, only the eligible listings
are shared to the party. For instance, if a listing is not eligible for a themed
party, it will be shared to your followers instead. Here‚Äôs an example of how
this works: * Share Listing 1 - This item is eligible for the party, so it‚Äôs
shared to the party. * Share Listing 2 - This item is not eligible for the
party, so it‚Äôs shared to your followers. * Share Listing 3 - This item is not
eligible for the party, so it‚Äôs shared to your followers. * Share Listing 4 -
This item is eligible for the party, so it‚Äôs shared to the party. * Share
Listing 5 - This item is eligible for the party, so it‚Äôs shared to the party.
However, during the 10 pm to 12 am party, all items are considered eligible and
are shared to the party, regardless of their theme. The app does not pre-select
the listings that will be shared to the party. Instead, it continues the cycle
of sharing and when the party time occurs, it shares the listings that are
eligible for that particular party. This means that the specific listings shared
to the party are determined by the timing of the party and the cycle of sharing,
rather than being pre-selected by the app. I hope this clarifies the process for
you. If you have any other questions or need further clarification, please don‚Äôt
hesitate to ask. Thank you so much! Kind regards, Mary

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-06T03:35:10Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Rose, Thank you for getting back to me. In the case of a reversal, you
will not see a refund credit on your statement you'll just see the original
authorization drop off your statement entirely after a few days. There will be
no payment and no refund. It'll appear as if the whole transaction never
happened. Your bank should be able to confirm this for you. Depending on your
card issuer, the original charge should have disappeared from their pending
charges. I hope this clarifies your concern. If you have any other questions or
need further assistance, please don‚Äôt hesitate to reach out. Best regards, Gail

your items, you'll have the ability to edit the prices of listings that you

Starting Price: -16+ You'll be able to edit the listing's starting price of $16
(discounted by 20%). Please note that you need to set up a ‚ÄúStarting Price‚Äù
first. After that, you can go to the ‚ÄúIndividual Pricing‚Äù page to change the

Subject: New message from "Posh Sidekick"
Created At: 2024-03-05T16:53:52Z

Threads:
Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-05T17:26:34Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Ashley, Thank you so much for reaching out! Please let me explain this
feature. This will represent the lowest possible discount you would want to give
on any item. If someone sends you an offer for more than what this value is, it
will automatically trigger. This represents how much of a counteroffer you will
send back, once the reserve price has been triggered. The counter-offer feature
becomes active when you receive a lowball offer that falls below the specified
minimum percentage threshold for countering. EXAMPLE: Let's say you've listed an
item for $60, and in your settings, you've established a minimum percentage
threshold to trigger a counteroffer at 50%, with a counteroffer percentage of
10%. When someone offers you $30 for that item, which is exactly 50% of the
original price, the counter-offer mechanism kicks in. It generates a
counter-offer of $54, representing a 10% discount off the initial price. The
counter-offer feature will not trigger if someone sends an offer that is above
the minimum percentage threshold you have set. In other words, it only comes
into play when an offer is at or below the specified threshold. For instance, in
this scenario, the counter-offer mechanism activates when an offer falls below
$30, which is less than 50% of the item's original price. Any offer exceeding
this 50% threshold will not trigger the counter-offer functionality. I hope you
find it helpful. If you still have any questions or concern, please let me know.
Have a great day! Best Regards, Simon

Created At: 2024-03-05T12:40:42Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Amanda, Thank you for reaching out! Individual pricing is a sub-option for
the Starting Price (Percentage off or Value Type) that you have set up. Once
you've configured a Starting Price for your items, you'll have the ability to
edit the prices of listings that you don't want to run with the Starting Price
discount or value. For example: Starting Price (Percentage off): 20% Individual
Pricing: Original Price: $20 Starting Price: -16+ You'll be able to edit the
listing's starting price of $16 (discounted by 20%). Please note that you need
to set up a ‚ÄúStarting Price‚Äù first. After that, you can go to the ‚ÄúIndividual
Pricing‚Äù page to change the price of specific items. This allows you to have
different prices for different items if needed. If you still have any questions
or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out. Thank you! Kind
regards, Simon

listings anytime as per your preference. This feature has been tested and has

sales. It‚Äôs a good fit for all niches and can definitely give your closet a

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-05T01:57:22Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Carissa, Thank you for sending the screenshot, Upon checking, the starting
price is set to 0. This is the reason why the app is running the items with
their original prices. Individual pricing is a sub-option for the Starting Price
(Percentage off or Value Type) that you have set up. Once you've configured a
Starting Price for your items, you can edit the prices of listings that you
don't want to run with the Starting Price discount or value. For example:
Starting Price (Percentage off): 20% Individual Pricing: Original Price: $20
Starting Price: -16+ You can edit the listing's starting price of $16
(discounted by 20%). Please note that you need to set up a ‚ÄúStarting Price‚Äù
first. After that, you can go to the ‚ÄúIndividual Pricing‚Äù page to change the
price of specific items. This allows you to have different prices for different
items if needed. If you still have any questions or need any more help, please

From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Leanna, Thank you so much for reaching out! Upon checking, you are
currently on a soft ban. Please keep in mind that it lasts for about 2-3 hours.
To avoid a soft ban, do not share your closet or add listings while the app is
sharing. This is because Poshmark sometimes considers this to be a high level of
activity in your closet. Please avoid using two sharing services at the same
time. Rest assured that the app will automatically resume sharing once the
restriction is lifted. Also, if you want to work on your closet, please disable
all sharing features to avoid this. I really hope you understand. Have a great
day! Best Regards, Simon

From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Christine, Thanks for reaching out! Upon reviewing your current settings,
I noticed that your self-sharing option is set to "randomize sharing," which
means the app shares your items randomly. However, the app should not include
sharing items that are already sold. If you notice the same problem, please send
us the link to the item sold so the technical team can investigate it. I also
recommend changing the setting to "share by in reverse." Go to your share
setting ( gear icon in the top left corner of the app). This adjustment will
ensure that the app shares from the bottom to the top of your closet, thereby
avoiding any confusion with sold listings. Thank you! Best, Julia

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-04T01:10:18Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Nancy, Thank you for reaching out! Upon checking, it appears that your
account was soft-banned. However, please don't worry, as the restriction for
your closet has been lifted. A soft ban means that your closet is temporarily
blocked from sharing or following by Poshmark due to excessive activity. This
can occur if you manually share or add new items while the app is already
sharing your listings or if you exceed the daily limits set by Poshmark. It's
important to note that this is not a serious issue, and it does not put your
account in any danger. The soft ban is simply an automated action taken by
Poshmark, and it can sometimes trigger without warning for minor reasons. Rest
assured that our app "Posh Sidekick" has built-in safety measures to handle
situations like this, and typically, the issue is resolved within 2 to 3 hours.
To prevent this from happening again, I suggest turning off the sharing features
of the app before sharing or adding new items to your closet. Once you've
finished sharing/adding items, you can then turn the sharing feature back on.
Thank you for your understanding! Sincerely, Dave

your closet is temporarily blocked by Poshmark from sharing or following due to
excessive activity. This can occur if you manually share or add new items while

by Poshmark. It's important to note that this is not a serious issue, and it
does not put your account in any danger. The soft ban is simply an automated
action taken by Poshmark, and it can sometimes trigger without warning for minor
reasons. Rest assured that our app "Posh Sidekick" has built-in safety measures
to handle situations like this, and typically, the issue is resolved within 2 to
3 hours. To prevent this from happening again, I suggest turning off the sharing
features of the app before sharing or adding new items to your closet. Once
you've finished sharing/adding items, you can then turn the sharing feature back
on. Pamela 15:02 Where is this feature I‚Äôm on my iphone Customer S. 15:03 It was

Hello Pamela, Thank you so much for reaching out! Upon checking, your closet was
on a soft ban. Please keep in mind that it lasts for about 2‚Äì3 hours. To avoid a
soft ban, do not share your closet or add listings while the app is sharing.
This is because Poshmark sometimes considers this to be a high level of activity
in your closet. Please avoid using two sharing services at the same time. I
confirm that your restriction has been lifted already and your closet is now
being shared. Please check it out now. Yes, our app will be sharing contacts,
except the app is not performing any other activity. I hope you understand. Have
a great day! Best Regards, Simon

edit them in anyway. I can't change the price, or change or add pictures, etc. I
have to delist and "sell similar." However, once I do that, it takes away the
number of listings that I can sell on ebay. Since I have had the app and listed
on ebay - I haven't made one sale. On kidizen - I also get error messages,
though not as many as mercari. Once the app relists an item for me, the pictures
are not clear (blurry) and have a green tone. I have no other choice but to
delete and make a whole new listing. But that deducts from my amount of listings
on the app (which is not fair). It also is time consuming. Also, if I "hide" a
listing as inactive, the app still relists it. So, if I don't search everyday to
look for items the app lists that should not be there - they are listed for
sale. This results in items being at risk of being sold that aren't available
for sale. I can't even remember the last time I made a sale on kidizen.
Additionally, on posh sidekick when I schedule a silent show and add my starting
prices to the listings - once the show starts - my prices are gone and I have to
manually go into the show and do it all over again. Additionally, the shows
freeze and it takes long to move from item to item. People leave my show due to
it freezing and they don't come back. In all the shows I had - I've only made
one sale. Furthermore, many times offers aren't sent after someone likes my item
and I have to search everyday from the night before to see what items were not
sent offers to the liker and send offers manually. These are the main issues.
Thank you. Best Regards, Missy

Disputes are a part of doing business online, but knowing that doesn't make them
any less frustrating to deal with. Unfortunately, once a bank decides that
you've lost a dispute, that decision is final. It seems you did not submit
evidence for this dispute. Remember that submitting evidence is your only chance
to win a dispute and recover your funds. Be sure to check our guides
[https://58.email.stripe.com/CL0/https:%2F%2Fstripe.com%2Fdocs%2Fdisputes%2Fcategories%23dispute-category-types/1/0100018dff462413-d1e892d0-0dc4-4496-b94a-e7ec374531b9-000000/F__FbyogIzqhAX0p4nYRb2AeS7GQpN-2K8HfzVTrFZA=342]
on how to submit the best evidence possible for each dispute reason. If you'd
like to know more about why you lost this particular dispute, the issuer has
provided some documentation with their decision that may shed some light on
their reasoning. You can view it on your Dashboard
[https://58.email.stripe.com/CL0/https:%2F%2Fdashboard.stripe.com%2Fb%2Facct_1JLARNFAgxGOpyBo%3Fdestination=%252Fpayments%252Fpi_3OdzmXFAgxGOpyBo1Dw1O6I2/2/0100018dff462413-d1e892d0-0dc4-4496-b94a-e7ec374531b9-000000/-14fu2q_aaSYXg5CEKjt-kywSsB0RrUwKs-2cQKfqQg=342]
now. We recognize that losing a dispute is painful. We are here to help and have
put together some resources below on what you can do to avoid disputes.

Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-03T17:21:05Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Staci, I hope you are doing great! I am here to update you regarding the
import issue you were encountering. I have heard back from the technical team,
and as per the team, this error message is from the eBay API. Actually, eBay
limits the time ranges to less than 120 days when getting items' lists. Please
select the range which is less than 120 days and then try to import. Let's
suppose you want to import items from Nov 1 in 2023, you can split the date
range to Nov 1, 2023 - Jan 1, 2024, and then in 2nd try choose Jan 2 - March 3.
I hope you understand. If you are still confused or need assistance, please let
me know. Have a great day! Best Regards, Simon

due to excessive activity. LMBALFOUR@LIVE.CA 23:32 Ok, thank you Customer S.

by Poshmark and can sometimes be triggered for minor reasons. But don‚Äôt worry,
our app, ‚ÄúPosh Sidekick‚Äù, has built-in safety measures to handle situations like
this. Typically, the issue is resolved within 2 to 3 hours. Customer S. 23:32 To

Type: customer
Created At: 2024-03-02T03:54:33Z
From: g3step@gmail.com
Body:
Hi Kate, I am canceling my subscription because of several reasons. Sidekick
only does 400 follows in 24 hours and I am spending between 2-3 hours every
night following other people and closets. I pay for a bot so I dont have to do
this. Poshmark allows up to 10k a day in follows (same amount as shares) and the
people who follow you are the ones who see your feed. You follow, they follow
back. You need to have followers to be successful at Poshmark, its not just
about sharing. Also, I tried the Crosslisting and that was just a mess. I never
could connect to all my accounts like Depop, Etsy, etc. and the two accounts it
did connect to took way to much time to upload all the required information for
each listing. And I did reach out to support, but it was not successful. The bot
I was using prior to Sidekick does 10K shares and 10K follows in a 24 hour
period and includes Crosslisting (among other thing) that was much more user
friendly and connected easily to my other acounts. I wanted to try Sidekick
because it sounded really great and I was hopeful it would meet my needs and
help increase sales. But unfortunately that has not been the case for me. On a
side note, Sidekick does have an awesome customer service team and I appreciate
all the FB posts and updates from Michael and Erica! Perhaps in the future I
will give Sidekick another try. Kind regards, Stephanie McClain

Hello Laura, Thank you so much for reaching out! I am sorry for the
inconvenience. Upon checking, your closet was on a soft ban. Please keep in mind
that it lasts for about 2‚Äì3 hours. To avoid a soft ban, do not share your closet

considers this to be a high level of activity in your closet. Please avoid using
two sharing services at the same time. Please don't worry; your closet
restriction has been lifted, and your closet is now being shared. Please check
it out now. I hope you understand. Have a great day! Best Regards, Simon

Subject: undefined
Created At: 2024-03-01T14:04:28Z

Threads:
Type: message
Created At: 2024-03-04T18:27:40Z
From: profitprofession@gmail.com
Body:
Hello Lisa, I hope this email finds you well. I am reaching out to you regarding
the concern you have reported and the technical team has an update. The app is
fetching your available items only for the next 5 days for relisting. Cannot
fetch not available items. If the app has already fetched the listing for
relisting, and you changed its status to NOT FOR SALE, the app will still relist
it as Poshmark allows Not For Sale items to be deleted and relisted. And because
the app has fetched the listing before as an available item. We suggest every
time you're going to change the status of your items, please check them also on
the View Upcoming Page for Relisting. You'll be able to view the list of
listings that are going to be relisted by the app for the next 5 days. If the
item is available there, you can remove it from the list so the app won't relist
it. You need to remove it after changing the listing status to not for sale. In
this way, the app won't relist the item and stop fetching the item for relist. I
hope this clarifies your concern. If you have any other questions or need
further assistance, please don‚Äôt hesitate to reach out. Best regards, Gail

Created At: 2024-03-01T14:43:45Z

to our technical team and once I have an update I will inform you promptly.

Hello Tracy, Thank you for reaching out! I‚Äôm sorry to hear about the issues
you‚Äôre experiencing with Posh Sidekick. This issue usually occurs when there
have been recent changes to your Poshmark account, such as updating your
password or changing your Poshmark closet name. To resolve this, you‚Äôll need to
relink your closet to the app. Here‚Äôs how: UNLINK - RELINK Go to Profile Page >
Click Switch Closet > Swipe left to Unlink > Then re-link your new closet Once
you‚Äôve done this, your items should start sharing again. If you continue to
experience issues, please let us know. We‚Äôre here to help! Best regards, Mary

experience. Here are some of the features you might find beneficial: 1. Self
Shares: Automatically share your own listings to increase visibility and
engagement. 2. Follow Back: Automatically follow back users who follow you,
maintaining a strong and engaged community. 3. Share Back: Automatically share
back the listings of users who share your items, fostering reciprocity. 4. Party
Sharing: Automatically share your listings to relevant parties to attract more
potential buyers. 5. Community Sharing: Share items from other users' closets
within the community to build connections and expand your reach. 6. Target
Follow Closets: Automatically follow specific closets to tailor your feed to
your preferences. But that's not all! We also offer more advanced features to
optimize your Poshmark experience: You can share closet category wise, color
wise You can set offer rules You can set relist rules Closet Snapshot Unfollow

Relists Blacklist Items from relist Remove Duplicates Promote Listings Sales
report with Sales map Background Removal Tool These features are designed to
enhance your Poshmark journey, save you time, and improve your overall selling
experience. Whenever you feel ready to explore these tools and take advantage of
their benefits, we'll be here to assist you every step of the way. We wish you
continued success! Best regards, Kate
